page.title: 01WYKEHAM HOUSE D BLOCK
page.content: Our D block is a rural area consisting of country lanes, woodland and farms.The Southampton to Portsmouth railway runs diagonally through the block.Part of the A3051 runs through two of the Western squares while in the East a minor road links Tapnage and Shedfield Common, one third of the area is covered by deciduous woodland with the largest extent being Botley Wood in the South. Two thirds of our area will be affected by the proposed Whiteley plan which will alter the nature of the D block if the plan goes through. { ARTS AND CRAFTS Nobody practises Arts and Crafts in our area.
